header.gameNote: BASKETBALL TRAVELERS CLASSIC AT SEATTLE WA

article.headline: Northern Iowa 83, Pepperdine 58
article.story: SEATTLE (AP) -- Travis Brown led a balanced Northern Iowa offense with 16 points, and the Panthers routed Pepperdine 83-58 on Monday in the second day of the Basketball Travelers Classic. The Panthers rebounded from a sluggish 68-63 win over Nicholls State in Sunday's opening round and flustered the Waves with tough defense and sharp shooting. Northern Iowa (2-0) shot 57 percent for the game, including 9-for-12 on 3-pointers. Brooks McKowen was the only other Panthers player in double figures with 11 points, but four players -- Eric Coleman, Stephen Jones, Kwadzo Ahelgegbe and Adam Koch -- all finished with nine points. Every Northern Iowa player who scored had at least six points. The Panthers led by as many as 35 in the second half before Pepperdine trimmed the final margin in the closing minutes. Northern Iowa also outrebounded the Waves 41-18 and scored 16 second-chance points. Marvin Lea led the Waves (0-2) with 22 points, but the Waves' offense shot just 36 percent a day after scoring 91 points on Washington. The Waves went 8:14 of the second half without a field goal, as the Panthers went on a 19-4 run extending their lead to 67-34. Pepperdine shot 45 percent against Washington, but missed 12 of its first 15 shots and never found an offensive rhythm as Northern Iowa built a 20-point lead by halftime. Kingsley Costain scored 12 points and Gregg Barlow had 10 for the Waves. Northern Iowa, an NCAA tournament team the last three years, will close out the three-day, round-robin tournament on Tuesday night against No. 17 Washington. Pepperdine will play Nicholls State.
